article.headline: Colgate handles Georgetown 34-14
article.story: WASHINGTON, D.C. -- Gavin McCarney passed for 248 yards and three touchdowns, and rushed for 109 yards, to lead Colgate over Georgetown 34-14 in a Patriot League contest. Colgate (3-5, 2-0) amassed 309 yards on the ground and limited Georgetown (1-7, 0-2) to a paltry 54 yards rushing. Demetrius Russell carried from 1 yard out to give Colgate the early advantage, but the extra-point attempt failed. The Hoyas took a short-lived lead later in the first quarter on Kyle Nolan's 55-yard TD pass to Zack Wilke. The Raiders answered with three consecutive touchdowns -- a 3-yard scoring strike from McCarney to C.J. Stempeck, McCarney's 12-yard run and a 5-yard TD toss to John Maddaluna. Georgetown cut into Colgate's lead with Nolan's 6-yard TD run, but the Raiders tacked on a fourth-quarter score as McCarney found Maddaluna for a 4-yard score, his second TD catch of the day.
